                <p>The Hong Kong Forum on Neutron Scattering is a conference series that focuses on specific aspects of neutron scattering science and their applications. The 2025 Forum will feature <strong>soft matter and complex materials</strong>, particularly in relation to scientific research and instrument development.</p>
                <p>Sponsored by the Croucher Foundation and the Center for Neutron Scattering at City University of Hong Kong (CityUHK), the 2025 Forum will gather leading experts from around the world in the fields of soft matter and biophysics, as well as specialists from major international neutron scattering facilities, to share their latest findings and discuss current issues.</p>
